{"id":26,"parent_id":0,"book_id":80,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":26,"title":"Chapter 23: Ammon: A Great Servant","subtitle":"","short_title":"Chapter 23","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant"},[".heading",{"id":"head1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.head1"},[".titleNumber","Chapter 23"],["h1","Ammon: A Great Servant"]],[".bodyBlock",[".image",{"id":"f1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.f1"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_026_01.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p3"},"The four sons of Mosiah left Zarahemla to teach the Lamanites the gospel. They each went to a different city."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p4"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/17.12-13"},"Alma 17:12–13"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f2","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.f2"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_026_02.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p5"},"Ammon went to the land of Ishmael. As he entered the city, the Lamanites tied him up and took him to their king, Lamoni."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p6"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/17.20-21"},"Alma 17:20–21"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.f3"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_026_03.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p7"},"Ammon told King Lamoni that he wanted to live among the Lamanites. Lamoni was pleased and had his men untie Ammon."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p8"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/17.22-24"},"Alma 17:22–24"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.f4"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_026_04.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p9"},"Ammon said he would be one of the king’s servants. The king sent him to watch his flocks."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p10"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/17.25"},"Alma 17:25"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.f5"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_026_05.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p11"},"One day while Ammon and some other servants were taking the flocks to get water, Lamanite robbers scattered the animals and tried to steal them."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p12"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/17.26-27"},"Alma 17:26–27"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/18.7"},"Alma 18:7"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.f6"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_026_06.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p13"},"The servants who were with Ammon were scared. King Lamoni had killed his other servants who had lost animals to these robbers."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p14"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/17.28"},"Alma 17:28"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.f7"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_026_07.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p15"},"Ammon knew this was his chance to use the Lord’s power to win the hearts of the Lamanites. Then they would listen to his teachings."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p16"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/17.29"},"Alma 17:29"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.f8"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_026_08.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p17"},"Ammon told the servants that if they gathered the scattered animals, the king would not kill them."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p18","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p18"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/17.31"},"Alma 17:31"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.f9"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_026_09.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p19","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p19"},"Ammon and the other servants quickly found the animals and drove them back to the watering place."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p20","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p20"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/17.32"},"Alma 17:32"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.f10"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_026_10.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p21","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p21"},"The Lamanite robbers came back. Ammon told the other servants to guard the flocks while he fought the robbers."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p22","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p22"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/17.33"},"Alma 17:33"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.f11"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_026_11.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p23","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p23"},"The Lamanite robbers were not afraid of Ammon. They thought they could easily kill him."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p24","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p24"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/17.35"},"Alma 17:35"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.f12"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_026_12.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p25","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p25"},"The power of God was with Ammon. He hit and killed some of the robbers with stones, which made the rest of the robbers very angry."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p26","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p26"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/17.35-36"},"Alma 17:35–36"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.f13"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_026_13.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p27","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p27"},"They tried to kill Ammon with their clubs, but each time a robber lifted a club to hit Ammon, he cut off the robber’s arm. Frightened, the robbers ran away."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p28","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p28"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/17.36-38"},"Alma 17:36–38"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.f14"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_026_14.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p29","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p29"},"The servants took the cut-off arms to King Lamoni and told him what Ammon had done."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p30","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p30"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/17.39"},"Alma 17:39"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/18.1"},"Alma 18:1"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.f15"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_026_15.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p31","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p31"},"The king was astonished at Ammon’s great power. He wanted to see Ammon but was afraid to because he thought Ammon was the Great Spirit."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p32","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p32"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/18.2-4,11"},"Alma 18:2–4, 11"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.f16"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_026_16.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p33","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p33"},"When Ammon did go in to see him, King Lamoni did not know what to say. He did not speak for an hour."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p34","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p34"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/18.14"},"Alma 18:14"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.f17"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_026_17.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p35","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p35"},"The Holy Ghost helped Ammon know what the king was thinking. Ammon explained that he was not the Great Spirit. He was a man."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p36","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p36"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/18.16-19"},"Alma 18:16–19"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f18","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.f18"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_026_18.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p37","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p37"},"The king offered Ammon anything he wanted if he would tell him what power he had used to defeat the robbers and to know the king’s thoughts."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p38","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p38"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/18.20-21"},"Alma 18:20–21"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f19","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.f19"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_026_19.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p39","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p39"},"Ammon said the only thing he wanted was for King Lamoni to believe what he would say. The king said he would believe everything Ammon told him."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p40","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p40"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/18.22-23"},"Alma 18:22–23"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f20","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.f20"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_026_20.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p41","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p41"},"Ammon asked King Lamoni if he believed in God. The king said he believed in a Great Spirit."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p42","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p42"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/18.24-27"},"Alma 18:24–27"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f21","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.f21"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_026_21.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p43","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p43"},"Ammon said that the Great Spirit is God, that he created everything in heaven and on the earth, and that he knows people’s thoughts."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p44","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p44"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/18.28-32"},"Alma 18:28–32"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f22","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.f22"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_026_22.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p45","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p45"},"Ammon said people were created in God’s image. He also said God had called him to teach the gospel to Lamoni and his people."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p46","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p46"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/18.34-35"},"Alma 18:34–35"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f23","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.f23"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_026_23.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p47","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p47"},"Using the scriptures, Ammon taught King Lamoni about the Creation, Adam, and Jesus Christ."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p48","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p48"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/18.36,39"},"Alma 18:36, 39"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f24","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.f24"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_026_24.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p49","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p49"},"King Lamoni believed Ammon and prayed to be forgiven of his sins. Then he fell to the ground and appeared to be dead."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p50","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p50"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/18.40-42"},"Alma 18:40–42"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f25","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.f25"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_026_25.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p51","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p51"},"Servants carried the king to his wife and laid him on a bed. After two days the servants thought he was dead and decided to bury him."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p52","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p52"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/18.43"},"Alma 18:43"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/19.1"},"Alma 19:1"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f26","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.f26"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_026_26.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p53","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p53"},"The queen did not believe that her husband was dead. Having heard of Ammon’s great power, she asked him to help the king."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p54","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p54"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/19.2-5"},"Alma 19:2–5"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f27","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.f27"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_026_27.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p55","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p55"},"Ammon knew Lamoni was under the power of God. He told the queen that Lamoni would awaken the next day."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p56","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p56"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/19.6-8"},"Alma 19:6–8"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f28","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.f28"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_026_28.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p57","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p57"},"She stayed by Lamoni’s side all night. The next day Lamoni got up and said he had seen Jesus Christ. The king and queen were filled with the Holy Ghost."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p58","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p58"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/19.11-13"},"Alma 19:11–13"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f29","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.f29"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_026_29.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p59","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p59"},"Lamoni taught his people about God and Jesus Christ. Those who believed repented of their sins and were baptized."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p60","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-23-ammon-a-great-servant.p60"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/19.31,35"},"Alma 19:31, 35"]]]]]]]],"refs":null}
